Lambda expression  is a anonymous function without name, without access modifier and without return type.
compiler will consider returned value automatically
syntax:   (n arguments)-> /*expression*/ ; 
	egs:  (a,b)->a+b;
	      ()->{System.Out.Println("hello");};
	      n->n*n;
	      n->{return n*n;};
Rules:  1. without curly braces we should not use return keyword
        2. if we want to return some value then we must use return keyword within curly braces
        3. if only one argument then parenthesis is optional      

Adv: will reduce code(concise code)


to call the lambda expression we must need functional interfaces

the interface which contains single abstract method and n no of default and static methods
to provide reference type to lambda expression we need FUNCTIONAL INTERFACE	      